## Paper Figures (5 Main + 1 Supplementary)

| # | Figure | RQ | Data | Core Message |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Pareto Frontier Overlay** | RQ1 | All pairs × BigCodeBench | Cascade is universally Pareto-optimal across model families |
| 2 | **Diversity-Gated vs Standard Cascade** | RQ2 | Phase 2 experiments | Cross-family disagreement is a stronger routing signal than self-confidence |
| 3 | **Homogeneous vs Heterogeneous Vote** | RQ2 | Cross-Family Vote vs Best-of-N | Diversity improves vote quality at same cost (or doesn't — both are publishable) |
| 4 | **Task Decomposition: Easy / Boundary / Unsolvable** | RQ3 | All pairs | Most tasks are trivially easy or globally unsolvable; narrow boundary explains saturation |
| 5 | **Strategy Ranking Shift: Agentic vs Non-agentic** | RQ1 | Pairs B,C,D × 2 benchmarks | Agentic tasks change optimal strategy (or don't) |
| S1 | **3-Tier vs 2-Tier Cascade** (supplementary) | RQ3 | 3-Tier experiment | Diminishing returns from finer-grained routing |

