## What Gets Dropped (Appendix or Omit)

| Finding | Disposition | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Self-critique hurts | Appendix (1 paragraph) | Well-known in literature, not our core story |
| Mamba-specific behavior | Fold into RQ2 diversity analysis | Only relevant if it supports/contradicts diversity thesis |
| Per-pair leaderboard tables | Supplementary material | Useful but not paper-body worthy |
| Architecture-specific escalation quirks | Appendix | Interesting but incremental |

---

## Risks and Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| GPT-OSS-20b doesn't support SGLang tool calling | Run BigCodeBench only; use vLLM fallback for MCP-Atlas |
| >2 model strategies actually outperform 2-model significantly | Adjust title/narrative to "When Three Heads..." — still publishable |
| Cross-family vote doesn't beat homogeneous Best-of-N | Negative result also supports thesis (diversity helps routing not voting) |
| Qwen3.5-9B too strong as "medium" (3-tier cascade trivially wins) | Use accuracy decomposition to show gains only on boundary tasks |
| MCP-Atlas pass rates too low for statistical significance | Use coverage_score as continuous metric instead of binary pass@1 |

---

## Key Implementation Notes

- All budget comparisons normalized to **GPU-seconds** (not wall-clock, not API cost)
- Diversity-Gated Cascade: new function needed in `combinations.py` — takes `small_cfgs: list[ModelConfig]` + `large_cfg: ModelConfig`
- Cross-Family Vote: modify existing `vote()` to accept heterogeneous model list
- 3-Tier Cascade: extend `cascade()` with `medium_cfg` parameter
- Confidence threshold calibration must use **held-out validation set** (not test set) to avoid reviewer concerns about tuning artifacts
